How do you want to create your Menu QR Code?

Select a QR code type

Select the type of QR code you need by clicking on the respective icon. You have up to 16 different options.

Change QR Code Type

Changing the QR code type is useful to update the content of your QR code without creating a new one. For instance, if your QR code currently redirects to an image gallery but you want it to redirect to a PDF, you can change the type from "Image" to "PDF".

When you switch the type, there's no need to reprint or download the QR code again. It will be updated automatically.

Add content to your QR code

Generate your Coupon QR code effortlessly. Create a special offer page, upload a coupon barcode, or input the coupon code text into the respective fields to personalize the discount people will access after they scan your coupon QR code.

Preview your QR code content

As you add content to your QR code, look at the phone on the right to visualize what people will see after scanning your QR code.

Pro tip: To view the full content of the page you created, simply scroll up and down within the phone preview.

At anytime, click on the [Preview] button below to visualize what people will see after scanning your QR code.

Change your QR code type

If youre not sure about the type of QR code you selected, simply click on the [Back] button to select another QR type that better fits your needs.

Go to the next step

Once you're satisfied with the content youve added to your QR code, click on the [Next] button to go to the next step and download your QR code.

Design your QR code

It is time to personalize your QR code. Change its design by adding a frame, selecting your preferred pattern style, adding your own logo and more.

Test your QR code design

Preview your QR code design

After youre done applying design changes to your QR Code, the final step should be to test it to ensure that it is readable. Just take out your mobile phone and aim the camera at the QR code.

Once youve made design adjustments to your QR code, click on the [Preview] button at any moment to see what your QR code looks like.
